<div class="post-date">Oct  4</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1159" title="Nice to see them fume for once"> Nice to see them fume for once</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>It seems like once every other week or so I get into arguments over Bush. </p>

	<p>This time I stepped into it simply not knowing the other guy was a big Bush fan. He said something akin to how the Hurricane Katrina relief effort was botched. I responded that we need to appoint professionals to positions like FEMA instead of Bush cronies with no experience. He then said I was being spun by the media and that it was Gov. Blanco who screwed up the relief effort.</p>

	<p>I tried to back out of it saying &#8220;let&#8217;s just appoint an independent panel to see where the errors occurred and correct them no matter who screwed up.&#8221; He argued &#8220;independent&#8221; doesn&#8217;t exist. Whatever. <br />
There&#8217;s no sense arguing with someone like that. </p>

	<p>Either way, this time it&#8217;s nice to see the conservatives fuming at Bush. With the nomination of Harriet Miers to the Supreme Court, it is the conservatives who suddenly feel sold out by Bush appointing a crony. </p>

	<p>I laughed when I read there are even rumblings from a few conservative senators about filibustering the choice. Wait, I thought the president deserved an up or down vote on his nominees.</p>

	<p>Who knows, maybe they&#8217;ll finally start to see the truth about the guy. He&#8217;s sold us all out.</p>

	<p>If you want a selective overview of what the conservative side has been saying, here&#8217;s a diary from <a href="http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2005/10/4/123124/331">Daily Kos.com</a></p>


 
