<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1149" title="The military was ready and the NWS gave the warning"> The military was ready and the NWS gave the warning</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>OK, so I won&#8217;t shut up.</p>

	<p>I just found out the military was waiting to help, but that <a href="http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2005/9/5/15109/84491">federal law said they couldn&#8217;t until the president said yes</a>. He didn&#8217;t. He was on vacation. On the bullshit meter, this rates a 10.</p>

	<p>Then, just to point out that ample warning was given to everyone who would listen that a killer hurricane was coming, a meteorologist outlines just a few of the <a href="http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2005/9/6/3840/39445">warnings given by the National Weather Service</a>.</p>

	<p>The bottom line is that Bush should have authorized military help <strong><em>before</em></strong> it hit. The military was ready, he was not. If Bush was a general he would have been dismissed and be facing a court martial no ands, ifs or buts.</p>


 
