<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1147" title="Want links to see why I&#39;m angry?"> Want links to see why I&#39;m angry?</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Let me count the ways&#8230;</p>

	<ol>
	<li><a href="http://news.ft.com/cms/s/84aa35cc-1da8-11da-b40b-00000e2511c8.html">FEMA won&#8217;t accept Amtrak&#8217;s help in evacuations</a>.</li>
		<li><a href="http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2005/9/5/105538/7048">FEMA turns away experienced firefighters</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/05/national/nationalspecial/05blame.html?ex=1283572800&en=1d14ebfbd942a7d0&ei=5090&partner=rssuserland&emc=rss">FEMA turns back Wal-Mart supply trucks</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/05/national/nationalspecial/05blame.html?ex=1283572800&en=1d14ebfbd942a7d0&ei=5090&partner=rssuserland&emc=rss">FEMA prevents Coast Guard from delivering diesel fuel</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/05246/565143.stm">FEMA won&#8217;t let Red Cross deliver food</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.zwire.com/site/news.cfm?newsid=15147862&BRD=1817&PAG=461&dept_id=68561&rfi=6">FEMA bars morticians from entering New Orleans</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2005/9/3/171718/0826">FEMA blocks 500-boat citizen flotilla from delivering aid</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/chi-0509040369sep04,1,4144825.story?ctrack=1&#38;cset=true">FEMA fails to utilize Navy ship with 600-bed hospital on board</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/chi-050902daley,1,2011979.story?coll=chi-news-hed">FEMA to Chicago: Send just one truck</a></li>
		<li><a href="http://www.fema.gov/news/newsrelease.fema?id=18470">FEMA: First Responders Urged Not To Respond</a></li>
	</ol>

	<p>Unfortunately, this is just the tip of the iceberg.</p>

	<p>Again, the Department of Homeland Security butchered the agency traditionally used for natural disaster relief and didn&#8217;t put anything in its place. Then Bush hired an attorney with no disaster management experience to run the shop. Incompetents.</p>

	<p>It&#8217;s just that so many, many good people have been chomping at the bit to help and haven&#8217;t been allowed to. At least they brought in an Army general that seems to be getting things going. I&#8217;ll give them credit for finally doing something right. </p>

	<p>I think relief is starting to happen (I hope). Thus I will shut up and let them do their work in peace. However, if the Bush administration starts to play the blame game or if they stonewall the needed investigation, then you better bet heads will roll.</p>

<strong>Note</strong>: I stole the list of links from DavidNYC who posted the list at <a href="http://www.dailykos.com/story/2005/9/5/16455/30830">Daily Kos</a>. I thank him for putting links to my frustrations. I&#8217;ll add more if I get the time.


 
